<p class="c34"><span class="c6">Tuesday 2nd April update - LyMá is aspirational for Europe. We want to encourage more people to dream big. However, it was our April fool.</span><span class="c6"><br><a href="">Read our Tuesday update on LinkedIn</a><br/><br/></span></p>

  <p class="c34"><span class="c8 c27">PRESS RELEASE - 8am Monday</span><span class="c6"><br>Lyon To M&aacute;laga Sleeper Train Service Launches</span></p>
  
  <p class="c3"><span class="c8"><br> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span class="c2">LyM&aacute;</span></p><p class="c1"><span class="c6"></span></p><p class="c3"><span class="c4">Departing 10:30pm from Lyon Part Dieu, France.</span></p><p class="c3"><span class="c4">8am - Arriving at M&aacute;laga Maria Zambrano, Spain<br><br>Boarding commences at 9:45pm, for those with dining car reservations, from 10pm. </span></p><p class="c1"><span class="c4"></span></p><p class="c3"><span class="c4">This 1800 km journey will whisk you from the centre of France, to the south of Spain&rsquo;s Andalucia.</span></p><p class="c1"><span class="c4"></span></p><p class="c3"><span class="c15">The first service will commence from 27th December, 2024 Lyon, arriving on 28th December, 2024 in time for the 12 grapes in </span><span class="c25">Plaza de la Constitucion</span><span class="c4">, M&aacute;laga and the New Year&rsquo;s eve celebrations.</span></p><p class="c1"><span class="c4"></span></p><p class="c3"><span class="c4">With the 3 Kings festivities on 6th January, there will be a return service on 7th January. Departing 22:30 M&aacute;laga, arriving 08:00 Lyon. </span></p>

<p class="c3 c24"><span class="c28">
<br> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; SIGNUP TO THE TOTRAVELTO.COM<br> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span><span class="c19"><a class="c18" href="https://totravelto.us21.list-manage.com/subscribe?u=1935f0c08c83da32612162ae7&id=46cb0ce0a0" target="_blank">NEWSLETTER</a></span><span class="c5"><br></span></p>


<p class="c1"><span class="c4"></span></p><p class="c3"><span style="overflow: hidden; display: inline-block; margin: 0.00px 0.00px; border: 0.00px solid #000000; transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); -webkit-transform: rotate(0.00rad) translateZ(0px); width: 624.00px; height: 624.00px;">
<img alt="artist impression of a purple euroduplex double decker train" src="/assets/image1-3c0dbb4a1a4ba1059e3da9899fffba7e2fa2aa5b8dcd14bf8dbb4af831d27ad3.png" width="624" height="624" />
</span></p><p class="c1"><span class="c4"></span></p><p class="c3"><span class="c8">Renowned for its Michelin Star restaurants, Lyon&rsquo;s acclaimed chef Monsieur Marcel Mariscos has prepared a special evening menu featuring freshly caught fish - </span><span class="c14">the </span><span class="c8 c29">Rh&ocirc;ne trout</span><span class="c14">. G</span><span class="c6">uests can also opt for a fantastic breakfast menu served from 7am - with final departures from the train at 8.30am.</span></p><p class="c1"><span class="c4"></span></p><p class="c3"><span class="c15">It will operate at 300 km/h and refurbished Duplex trains &nbsp;painted &nbsp;in a luxury purple livery. Inspired by OUIGOs reuse of double decker trains in Spain, and also OBB&rsquo;s recent innovations with its Night Jet service, there will be a mix of sleeping accommodations from double rooms, family rooms, and private Japanese-style sleeping pods. <br><br></span><span class="c0">Connecting services<br></span></p><p class="c3"><span class="c15">Geneva (3h), </span><span class="c4">Frankfurt (6h) and Paris (2h) are within reach by train, from Lyon.<br></span></p><p class="c3"><span class="c4">M&aacute;laga&rsquo;s coast has its own Cercanias rail line. Day trips to Ronda, Granada &amp; Cordoba are enjoyable. &nbsp;</span></p><p class="c1"><span class="c4"></span></p><p class="c3"><span class="c15 c26">&ldquo;Whilst working on ToTravelTo.com&rsquo;s European train trip planning and booking site, we realised that what is lacking is a service connecting the two great cities of Lyon and M&aacute;laga.&rdquo; (Founder, Ian). &ldquo;After the inaugural service, we will quickly expand to running 3 times a week, with further expansion options for the Summer months.&rdquo;<br><br>We have been inspired by Elmer of European Sleeper, who achieved their dream of connecting 4 capital cities by night train, and the blog from Midnight Trains.</span></p><p class="c1"><span class="c4"></span></p><p class="c3"><span class="c15">For full details please sign up to our newsletter &amp; wait list at </span><span class="c15 c27 c30"><a class="c18" href="https://totravelto.com">https://totravelto.com</a></span><span class="c4">&nbsp;<br></span></p><p class="c1"><span class="c4"></span></p><p class="c3"><span class="c15"><br></span><span class="c0">Further Details</span></p><p class="c3"><span class="c8 c27"><br></span><span class="c32 c33">&quot;Creating the perfect dining experience for this magnificent journey has been a passion project for me. We&#39;ve curated a menu that harmonises with the rhythm of Spanish dining, embracing the late hours and the zest for life that is so quintessentially Spanish. For April, a special month that sings the praises of spring, I&#39;m particularly excited about our trout fish course. Sourced from the freshest catches, it reflects both the bounty of the </span><span class="c29 c32">Rh&ocirc;ne</span><span class="c29 c35">&nbsp;</span><span class="c7">and the culinary creativity that diners expect from a Michelin-level experience. This dish, among others, is designed to enchant our guests, making their travel not just a journey, but a celebration of European gastronomy.&quot; - Chef &Eacute;tienne Marcel Mariscos, noting his excitement about the curated dining experience aboard the train, especially the April fish course.</span></p><p class="c1"><span class="c0"></span></p>

<p class="c3 c24"><span class="c28">
